channel.title: Latest News and News Headlines | Daily Telegraph

item.title: $1m reward to solve bikie assassination
item.description: A reward of up to $1 million is being offered for information that helps solve the assassination of Rebels bikie president Nick Martin, who was shot during a drag racing event in Perth.

item.title: Housemate ‘took secret, intimate photos’
item.description: A man has been slapped with charges for allegedly hiding a camera in his housemate’s wardrobe and capturing a huge amount of intimate images of her without her knowing.

item.title: Worker killed at WA gold mine
item.description: A worker has died after an incident at Westgold Resources’ Big Bell underground mine in WA’s Mid West region.

item.title: Minor slip ups may be behind SA outbreak
item.description: The investigation into how three South Australian medi-hotel staff members contracted coronavirus, later throwing the state into lockdown, is almost complete.

item.title: Giant spider in Woolies gingerbread
item.description: A Sydney mum said she’s been “in hysterics all day” following the reaction to her terrifying find in a Woolworths gingerbread house.

item.title: Competition ‘concern’ over Woolies deal
item.description: Woolworths’ planned deal with a family-owned wholesale food distributor is a concern to the competition watchdog, which says it will likely increase the supermarket giant’s leverage with manufacturers.

item.title: Fire on Melbourne CBD building rooftop
item.description: Thick smoke was billowing from a fire on the roof of a Melbourne building on Tuesday afternoon.

item.title: ‘Clown’: Insults fly over sex scandal
item.description: Labor has branded Paul Fletcher a “clown” and demanded the Prime Minister “pull him into line”, after ABC chair Ita Buttrose accused the Communications Minister of political interference.

item.title: MP’s eye-watering bill for family trip
item.description: A member of NSW parliament billed taxpayers for a flight to a family event, it has been revealed.

item.title: Big Brother contestant behind bars
item.description: Less than five months after he narrowly avoided jail over a string of drugs and weapons charges, season eight Big Brother contestant Saxon Pepper is behind bars.
